metadata.name: Urban Flora #484
metadata.description:
Urban Flora is a generative artwork exploring interplay of natural and artificial forms created by Marcin Ignac / @marcinignac

http://marcinignac.com/projects/urban-flora/

The project was inspired by the 3/4/5G network infrastructure more and more present in the parks and greenery of our cities. Final Urban Flora transformed into a study of abandoned structures of a long forgotten civilisation.

The whole image is generative and/or procedural. Leaves are parametric, twigs and trees use the space colonisation algorithm, and the geometry is based on platonic solids transformed though series of operations.

Features determined at the time of minting:
- one of the platonic solids or a prism
- one of 15 geometry transformations
- a color theme
- leaves or detailed twigs
- leaf's spread and the amount of ridges

'g' / 'tree finger tap' - resolution and export
'drag' - rotate
'scroll' - zoom (on desktop)

Please note the project needs a decent GPU.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

--
With dedication to my wife.

metadata.name: BW V/1 #37
metadata.description:
Generally, pixel values are represented by a byte (8b) after quantization. If the gray value with continuous black-gray-white changes is quantized into 256 gray levels, the gray value ranges from 0 to 255, indicating that the brightness is from dark to light, and the color in the corresponding image is from black to white. Black and white photos contain all shades of gray between black and white, with each pixel value being one of 256 shades of gray between black and white.

I divided a circle into four equal parts.
Their centers are placed at the four corners of the square.It diverges from each center point,The color gets lighter as the circle gets larger in diameter.
Simple methods can produce special patterns.
Test.

metadata.name: Action Fields #40
metadata.description:
A generative painting based on abstract expressionism and the action paintings of Jackson Pollock.

Several different flow fields are used to create paths which are then painted in one of four different styles (pastel, paint, Pollock, black+gold). Additional features affect the background, path length + angles, level of detail, and mess (drips and splats). 

NOTES: 
- Some variations of the Pollock style may appear slightly different between browsers, but will render consistently in the same browser. 
- On slower devices, it may take some time to being drawing due to the background rendering.
- If you get a browser warning that the page is taking a long time, press continue.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1200x928px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution from 300 to 5,000 px. The ideal higher resolution is 2,000px.

metadata.name: Bad Habits #113
metadata.description:
Get into Bad Habits...
  
Bad Habits is a collaboration project between me and evilnft.

This is a lottery style png layers project with generated background and layout.  

(illustrations by me / code by evilnft)

 - 20 illustrations
 - 10 text banners
- 8 layouts
- 2 layout styles : sketchy, blocks 
- 5 background colors  : eggshell, cheap pink, cheap craft, zancan, b&w
- 4 overall styles : tough luck, pink dreams, the zancan, black & white
